Shape memory polymer (SMP) is known to be a smart material that can alter its shape in order to respond to the exterior stimuli such as electricity, temperature, light and chemicals. These materials are being advanced for a extensive range of applications in biomedical, aerospace, automotive, and several other industries.

Major factors that are expected to boost the growth of the shape memory polymer market in the forecast period are the possible applications of shape memory polymers in the biomedical industry. Furthermore, the rise in the shape memory polymer requirement in the automotive and aerospace sector is further anticipated to propel the growth of the shape memory polymer market. On the other hand, the rise in the level of technological knowledge needed for the production of shape memory polymer is further projected to impede the growth of the shape memory polymer market in the timeline period.

In addition, the advancement and growth in the research and development activity in various sectors around the world will further provide potential opportunities for the growth of the shape memory polymer market. However, the impression of COVID-19 pandemic outbreak might further challenge the growth of the shape memory polymer market in the near future.

